      "title": "Configuration Guide",
      "stepTypesTitle": "Step Types",
      "stepTypeGate": "Gate — A decision point where the assigned role chooses the next step (e.g. accept / reject / advance). No file upload involved.",
      "stepTypeReview": "Review — The assigned role reviews the audio, marks issues, and makes a decision when done.",
      "stepTypeRevision": "Revision — The submitter uploads a new source version in response to issues. After upload, the track automatically returns to the linked review step.",
      "stepTypeDelivery": "Delivery — The assigned role uploads a deliverable (e.g. mastered audio). May include decision transitions.",
      "rolesTitle": "Role Assignment",
      "rolesDesc": "Each step requires an assigned role. \"Producer\" and \"Mastering Engineer\" correspond to fixed album members. \"Peer Reviewer\" is randomly assigned when the track enters review. \"Submitter\" is the original author of the track.",
      "transitionsTitle": "Transitions",
      "transitionsDesc": "Transitions define the paths from the current step to the next. Each transition has a \"decision name\" (e.g. accept, reject) and a \"target step\". The target can be another step's ID or one of three special terminal states: Completed, Rejected (final), or Rejected (resubmittable).",
      "revisionTitle": "Return To & Paired Revision Step",
      "revisionDesc": "Revision steps must have a \"Return To\" setting, which determines where the track goes after the submitter uploads. Review / Delivery steps can optionally set a \"Paired Revision Step\" so the system can route to the right revision step when needed.",
      "notesTitle": "Important Notes",
      "note1": "Workflows are locked once the album is created and cannot be changed afterward. Review carefully before creating.",
      "note2": "Step IDs must be unique and use only lowercase letters, numbers, and underscores.",
      "note3": "There must be at least one path leading to \"Completed\", otherwise tracks cannot finish."
    }
